HQINVESTMENT ISP Billing — MikroTik Hotspot Login Portal
==========================================================

Version : 2.0
Date    : 2025
Author  : HQINVESTMENT ISP Billing System

FILES INCLUDED
--------------
  login.html    - Main login page (M-Pesa payment + CHAP login)
  logout.html   - Logout confirmation page
  status.html   - Connection status page (auto-refreshes)
  error.html    - Single error display page
  errors.html   - Multiple errors display page
  redirect.html - Post-login redirect page
  rlogin.html   - RADIUS/account-based login page
  radvert.html  - Post-login advertisement page
  tandc.html    - Terms and conditions
  faqs.html     - Frequently asked questions
  md5.js        - MD5 library for CHAP authentication (REQUIRED)
  readme        - This file
  favicon.ico   - Site favicon

  assets/
    css/
      style.css - Main stylesheet
    img/
      (place logo and background images here)
    xml/
      hotspot.xml - Hotspot configuration metadata

HOW TO INSTALL ON MIKROTIK
---------------------------
1. Open Winbox → Files
2. Upload the entire "hotspot" folder to your MikroTik flash memory
3. Verify via Terminal:
     /file print where name~"hotspot"
4. Set your hotspot profile to use this directory:
     /ip hotspot profile set [find] html-directory=hotspot
5. Test by connecting a device to the hotspot WiFi

AUTHENTICATION METHODS SUPPORTED
----------------------------------
  - HTTP-CHAP  (secure, uses md5.js — RECOMMENDED)
  - HTTP-PAP   (plain text, less secure)
  - Cookie     (auto-login on return visits)
  - MAC-Cookie (auto-login by MAC address)

BILLING API ENDPOINTS USED
----------------------------
  POST /api/hotspot/purchase    - Initiate M-Pesa payment
  GET  /api/hotspot/status      - Poll payment status
  GET  /api/packages            - Fetch available packages

WALLED GARDEN (must be configured on MikroTik)
------------------------------------------------
  Add your billing server domain/IP to walled garden so
  unauthenticated users can reach the API:
    /ip hotspot walled-garden add dst-host="your-droplet-ip" action=allow
    /ip hotspot walled-garden ip add dst-address="your-droplet-ip" action=accept

